WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.980 --> 00:00:08.109
SPEAKER: So this
event is sort of

00:00:08.109 --> 00:00:11.200
to highlight some of the work
being done around LGBT youth

00:00:11.200 --> 00:00:13.432
work by an organization
called Lambda Legal.

00:00:13.432 --> 00:00:15.640
Many of you guys may be
familiar with Lambda already.

00:00:15.640 --> 00:00:18.850
They've been around since
1973 with the primary goal

00:00:18.850 --> 00:00:21.580
of fighting for full
equality for LGBT people

00:00:21.580 --> 00:00:24.820
and those living with HIV,
through primarily impact

00:00:24.820 --> 00:00:28.300
litigation and then also
education and policy work.

00:00:28.300 --> 00:00:29.745
So they're based in New York.

00:00:29.745 --> 00:00:31.870
They have presence in a
few other cities in the US.

00:00:31.870 --> 00:00:34.078
And they're in the process
of opening an office in DC

00:00:34.078 --> 00:00:34.914
right now.

00:00:34.914 --> 00:00:36.580
Given the kind of new
political climate,

00:00:36.580 --> 00:00:39.420
there's a lot of work to be
done there, as you guys know.

00:00:39.420 --> 00:00:42.155
So that process is ongoing.

00:00:42.155 --> 00:00:43.780
And one note that
was pointed out to me

00:00:43.780 --> 00:00:46.810
is that Lambda has won a
lot of their big victories

00:00:46.810 --> 00:00:48.760
during hostile administrations.

00:00:48.760 --> 00:00:49.570
It can be done.

00:00:49.570 --> 00:00:52.480
And will continue to
be done, as judiciary

00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:56.620
is a really important path
for us to make progress.

00:00:56.620 --> 00:00:59.346
So since we're talking
about LGBT youth today,

00:00:59.346 --> 00:01:01.720
I'd like to introduce you to
Currey Cook, who is actually

00:01:01.720 --> 00:01:04.209
the Director of the Youth
in Out-of-Home Care Project.

00:01:04.209 --> 00:01:06.340
He's also a staff
council at Lambda,

00:01:06.340 --> 00:01:08.740
which means he's a lawyer.

00:01:08.740 --> 00:01:11.680
And he has a lot of experience
working with LGBT youth.

00:01:11.680 --> 00:01:13.180
So before this,
he was co-director

00:01:13.180 --> 00:01:14.888
of the Bronx office
of the Children's Law

00:01:14.888 --> 00:01:16.167
Center in New York.

00:01:16.167 --> 00:01:18.750
He's also been a consultant to
the National Juvenile Defenders

00:01:18.750 --> 00:01:20.410
Center in Washington.

00:01:20.410 --> 00:01:22.090
He worked in Burundi
on an initiative

00:01:22.090 --> 00:01:25.030
to assist with reintegration
of former child soldiers

00:01:25.030 --> 00:01:26.860
into society.

00:01:26.860 --> 00:01:28.850
And before that, he spent
12 years in New York

00:01:28.850 --> 00:01:31.000
as an attorney for children
in foster care and juvenile

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:31.360
justice.

00:01:31.360 --> 00:01:33.220
So he has a lot of
experience in this field.

00:01:33.220 --> 00:01:35.710
There's no one better to
speak to us about this.

00:01:35.710 --> 00:01:37.332
Mr. Currey Cook.

