01:01:06.230 --> 01:01:09.650
through the federal agency is
going to be about screening out

01:01:09.650 --> 01:01:13.460
more and more people, which
is already just a really

01:01:13.460 --> 01:01:14.690
subjective process.

01:01:14.690 --> 01:01:17.390
But we know that we're having
this sort of word on high,

01:01:17.390 --> 01:01:21.380
like, find more people, do
more raids, deport more people,

01:01:21.380 --> 01:01:23.780
limit the number of
children that are coming in,

01:01:23.780 --> 01:01:25.980
all of these things
that cut out people.

01:01:25.980 --> 01:01:27.590
So I'm really
concerned that that's

01:01:27.590 --> 01:01:30.740
going to play in there in
that administrative process.

01:01:30.740 --> 01:01:33.890
In the court system, at least
you've got kind of levels,

01:01:33.890 --> 01:01:36.260
right, of a judicial
officer and other folks

01:01:36.260 --> 01:01:37.690
that are overseeing some cases.

01:01:37.690 --> 01:01:40.190
So, in theory, anyway, there
should be some more protections

01:01:40.190 --> 01:01:41.202
there.

01:01:41.202 --> 01:01:43.410
ALEX: You know, we're talking
about things we can do.

01:01:43.410 --> 01:01:45.890
And there are these sort of
organizational institutional

01:01:45.890 --> 01:01:48.200
things we could do, like
